                                            A bad first impression, but I get it now.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>This year marked Google Photos' 10th birthday, and to celebrate, a redesign was announced. The most noticeable changes appeared in the editor, and after initially being very against this change, it's really grown on me over time. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 14:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/i-thought-google-photos-ruined-the-editor-but-it-won-me-over/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Is It Safe to Keep a Portable Battery in a Hot Car?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/is-it-safe-to-keep-a-portable-battery-in-a-hot-car/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/portable-battery-overheating-on-a-car-dashboard-with-warning-icon-and-smoke.png" length="2442" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Accessories]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You probably should think twice about leaving that battery there.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>People leave portable batteries in their cars for emergencies or to recharge their phones on the go. After all, a car seems like the perfect mobile storage unit, ready to shuttle our gadgets wherever we need them. However, this is a huge mistake that can cost you a lot of money.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 23 Sep 2025 13:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/is-it-safe-to-keep-a-portable-battery-in-a-hot-car/</guid></item></channel>
